    "description": [
        "Episode number 2 of Series \"Planet Earth\". Program 2 of a 4 part series. Each program is divided into sections for easy classroom viewing using a combination of the latest computer graphics and filmed examples of climatic occurrences to provide a detailed description and explanation of the geographical factors influencing Planet Earth. This video aims to provide a detailed description and explanation of temperature. In particular it covers the ares of: the Earth's axis; day and night; latitude; aspect and altitude; ocean currents; prevailing winds; cloud cover and atmosphere, as well a contextual overview of the solar system. Includes a teacher's guide."
